###########################################################################
#  graphic_polar_plot - a polar rose r = cos(3*theta) traced inside a     #
#  raw @Graphic by emitting moveto/lineto over a parametric sweep.  The   #
#  @Graph package is cartesian-only (no native pie/polar mode), so this   #
#  exercises the embedded PS interpreter's `for`, `sin`, `cos`, `mul`,    #
#  `div`, `add` and CTM-translate path in z53.c on a curve that closes   #
#  on itself multiple times.                                              #
###########################################################################

@SysInclude { doc }
@Doc @Text @Begin
@PP
A polar rose r = cos(3 theta), traced as a piecewise-linear sweep:
@DP
@CentredDisplay {
   "gsave"
   "  xsize 2 div ysize 2 div translate"
   "  /scale ysize 2 div 4 sub def"
   "  0.2 0.4 0.8 setrgbcolor 0.8 setlinewidth"
   "  newpath"
   "  0 1 360 {"
   "     /theta exch def"
   "     /r theta 3 mul cos def"
   "     /x theta cos r mul scale mul def"
   "     /y theta sin r mul scale mul def"
   "     theta 0 eq { x y moveto } { x y lineto } ifelse"
   "  } for"
   "  stroke"
   "grestore"
} @Graphic { 5c @Wide 5c @High }
@End @Text
